{"lemma":"مُعَقِّبِي","slug":"مُعَقِّبِي","root":"ع.ق.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُعَقِّب","root":"عقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29856","n29857","n29858","n29859","n29860"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29856","headword_ar":"مُعْقَبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[appears, from what here follows, to be used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEoqabN HaAluhu","text_ar":"مُعْقَبٌ حَالُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose state is changed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. IAar cites as an ex. of this word,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kul~u HaY~K muEoqabN EuqabaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every living being"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comes to a state different from that in which he was"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by turns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29857","headword_ar":"مُعْقِبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to the O,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEoqabN","text_ar":"مِعْقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this I think a mistranscription,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A star that succeeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rises after, another star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and on the rising of which, he who rides in his turn, after another, mounts the beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a star at the appearance of which two persons who ride by turns during a journey take each the other's place; when one star sets and another rises, he who was walking mounts the beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiybN","text_ar":"عَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  See also 4, latter half; where an ex. occurs in a verse."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n29858","headword_ar":"مِعْقَبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"He"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is brought up for the office of Khaleefeh after the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actual"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Imám"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Khaleefeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A skilful driver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b3-  And A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is ridden by different persons in turns."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, * TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximaAr","text_ar":"خِمَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"muffler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head-covering"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (IAar, O, * K, TA;) so called because it takes the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaA='ap","text_ar":"مُلَا=ءَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ear-drop;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroTN","text_ar":"قُرْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29859","headword_ar":"مُعَقَّبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is made to go forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in the CK,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who goes forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, and so in my MS. copy of the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the shop of the vintner when a greater man than he enters."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaq~abFA","text_ar":"مُعَقَّبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came at the end,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"close, of the day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidoHN muEaq~abN","text_ar":"قِدْحٌ مُعَقَّبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is returned into the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbap","text_ar":"رِبَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time after time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the prize allotted to which is hoped for. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuwrN saHuwfu AlmuEaq~abi","text_ar":"جَزُورٌ سَحُوفُ المُعَقَّبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fat slaughtered camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEolN muEaq~abapN","text_ar":"نَعْلٌ مُعَقَّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sandal having an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqib","text_ar":"عَقِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29860","headword_ar":"مُعَقِّبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Coming after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near after, another thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiybN","text_ar":"عَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  It is said that it is applied as an epithet to an angel; that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaka muEaq~ibN","text_ar":"مَلَكَ مُعَقِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An angel that follows another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAy^ikapN muEaq~ibapN","text_ar":"مَلَايِكَةٌ مُعَقِّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaq~ibaAtN","text_ar":"مُعَقِّبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. pl. (O.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEaq~ibaAtu","text_ar":"المُعَقِّبَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The angels of the night and the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) because they succeed one another by turns; and the fem. form is used because of the frequency of their doing so, in like manner as it is in the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nas~aAbapN","text_ar":"نَسَّابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aAmapN","text_ar":"عَلَّامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the angles called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHafaZapu","text_ar":"الحَفَظَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAfiZN","text_ar":"حَافِظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: so in the Kur xiii. 12: in which some of the Arabs of the desert read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqiybu","text_ar":"مَعَاقِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) this [may be an anomalous pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiybN","text_ar":"عَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahaAjiynu","text_ar":"مَهَاجِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajiynN","text_ar":"هَجِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or it] is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaq~ibN","text_ar":"مُعَقِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaq~ibapN","text_ar":"مُعَقِّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being to compensate for the suppression of one of the two"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEaq~ibaAtu","text_ar":"المُعَقِّبَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camels that stand behind those that are pressing towards the wateringtrough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank; so that when one she-camel goes away, another comes in her place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ejaculations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which follow"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2104},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repeated at the end of the ordinary prayer, thirty-three in number, and which are followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AaloHamodu lil~`hi","text_ar":"اَلْحَمْدُ لِلّٰهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty-three times, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^akobaro","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirty-four times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaq~ibN","text_ar":"مُعَقِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who makes repeatedly warring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warring and plundering, expeditions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who journeys repeatedly, and does not stay with his family after his return."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who seeks after a thing repeatedly, striving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerting himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who follows after a thing that is his due, demanding restitution of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who follows close after a man, for something that is his due:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who seeks to recover his right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who, being despoiled of all his property in a hostile attack, makes a hostile attack upon him from whom he has thus suffered, and endeavours to recover his property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Lebeed says, describing a [wild] he-ass and his female,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Hat~aY tahaj~ara biAlr~awaAHi wahaAjahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        Talaba AlmuEaq~ibi Haq~ahu AlmuZoluwmu"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, but in the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alr~awaAHi","text_ar":"فِى الرَّوَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Until he went along in the midday heat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAlrwAH","text_ar":"بالرواح"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrwAH","text_ar":"الرواح"},{"kind":"text","text":"being redundant,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and drove her on"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by a pursuit]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the seeking of him who is making repeated efforts, having been wronged, to obtain his due:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmZlwm","text_ar":"المظلوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet qualifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmEq~b","text_ar":"المعقّب"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is in the nom. case agreeable with the meaning, (S, O,) because it is put after its proper place; (O;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmEq~b","text_ar":"المعقّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is literally in the gen. case, but as to the meaning is an agent: (S, O: *) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmEq~b","text_ar":"المعقّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the debtor who puts off the payment of his debt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmZlwm","text_ar":"المظلوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an agent and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmEq~b","text_ar":"المعقّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an objective complement: (S:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmEq~b","text_ar":"المعقّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who demands the payment of a debt and repeats his demand thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  Also Any one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. to the doing of a thing]. (O.) ―         -b8-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqibN","text_ar":"مَعَاقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA muEaq~iba liHukomihi","text_ar":"لَا مُعَقِّبَ لِحُكْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xiii. 41], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no repeller of his decree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who descends into a well to raise a stone of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAb","text_ar":"عُقَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also the verb.]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}